{
  "texts": [
    "But for applications where anatomical knowledge is crucial, the regional portions could not have the contextual details needed (e.g.",
    "white matter lesion segmentation).",
    "Ghafoorian et al. [274] employed non-uniformly observed patches to address this issue by significantly reducing sampling frequency on patch ends to encompass a wider context.",
    "Multi-scale investigation and the synthesis of images in a fully-connected layer are alternate methods that are employed by numerous entities.",
    "Despite the fact that all of the investigated research used 3-dimensional volumes of brain imaging, the majority of approaches only analyze the 3-dimensional volumes slice-by-slice."
  ]
}